    <p>New En­coun­ters/New Works Fea­tur­ing Lawrence Ypil</p>
    <p>As part of his Jalan Be­sar Writ­ing Res­i­dency, Filipino poet and es­say­ist Lawrence Ypil leads an on­line South-east Asian read­ing group to re­visit clas­sic and con­tem­po­rary English fic­tion from the Philip­pines. They will dis­cuss text ex­cerpts and their re­sponses to the sto­ries. A ques­tion-and-an­swer seg­ment will fol­low.</p>
    <p>Sing Lit Sta­tion’s Face­book Aug 26, 8pm</p>
    <p>Free; do­na­tion to Sing Lit Sta­tion (at giv­ing.sg) is en­cour­aged</p>
    <p>bit.ly/2DSy6no</p>
    <p>Read­ers’ Favourite</p>
    <p>Read­ers can vote for their favourite Chi­nese, English, Malay and Tamil short­listed books to be crowned the first Sin­ga­pore Lit­er­a­ture Prize Read­ers’ Favourite. They stand to win $50 in book vouch­ers from on­line book­store lo­cal­books.sg if they vote for a win­ning book. The writ­ers of the win­ning books will get $1,000 each.</p>
    <p>Vote by Mon; re­sults will be an­nounced on Aug 27, 8pm</p>
    <p>bit.ly/2XSBo12</p>
    <p>Po­etry Fes­ti­val Sin­ga­pore</p>
    <p>Lit­er­ary heavy­weights Des­mond Kon Zhicheng-Mingde, Koh Tai Ann and Yeow Kai Chai dis­cuss their in­sights into the chang­ing state of Sin­ga­pore po­etry in this on­line event fa­cil­i­tated by poet Mar­garet De­vada­son.</p>
    <p>Aug 29, 2.30pm</p>
    <p>Free bit.ly/3fUq76h</p>


